sun.jvm.hotspot.debugger.win32.coff

Interface COMDATSelectionTypes


  • public interface COMDATSelectionTypes
    Enumerates the COMDAT selection types. One of these is returned from AuxSectionDefinitionsRecord.getSelection().

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY
      Any section defining the same COMDAT symbol may be linked; the rest are removed.
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE
      The section is linked if a certain other COMDAT section is linked.
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_EXACT_MATCH
      The linker chooses an arbitrary section among the definitions for this symbol.
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_LARGEST
      The linker chooses the largest from the definitions for this symbol.
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_NODUPLICATES
      The linker issues a multiply defined symbol error if this symbol is already defined.
      static byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_SAME_SIZE
      The linker chooses an arbitrary section among the definitions for this symbol.

      • IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_EXACT_MATCH

        static final byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_EXACT_MATCH
        The linker chooses an arbitrary section among the definitions for this symbol. A multiply defined symbol error is issued if all definitions don't match exactly.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE

        static final byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE
        The section is linked if a certain other COMDAT section is linked. This other section is indicated by the Number field of the auxiliary symbol record for the section definition. Use of this setting is useful for definitions that have components in multiple sections (for example, code in one and data in another), but where all must be linked or discarded as a set.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_LARGEST

        static final byte IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_LARGEST
        The linker chooses the largest from the definitions for this symbol. If multiple definitions have this size the choice between them is arbitrary.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
